column20:
Dear United States Supreme Court Chief Justice John G. Roberts::: Jr::: Justice Clarence Thomas::: Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg::: Justice Stephen G. Breyer::: Justice Samuel A. Alito::: Jr::: Justice Sonia Sotomayor::: Justice Elena Kagan::: Justice Neil M. Gorsuch::: and Justice Brett M. Kavanaugh: the qualified immunity doctrine must be abolished or significantly modified for the following palpable reasons:
1. The judicial doctrine was created improperly by the judiciary infringing upon the legislatures role to create law. In effect::: the qualified immunity doctrine is the judicial branch improperly passing legislation;
2. Government officials have abused the doctrine to immunize themselves from abuse of power and unconstitutiona
l official misconduct;
3. The doctrine is inconsistently applied by the U.S. Circuit Courts of Appeals around the country;
4. Citizens of the United States have unjustly suffered violation of their civil rights for over 40 years::: since the doctrine was adopted; and
5. In one week municipal insurance companies and States have sustained financial losses exceeding the savings the doctrine has unjustly handed to governmental entities and officials over the last 40 years.

LET THE PROTESTS BEGIN AT THE DOORSTEPS OF THE UNITED STATES SUPREME COURT!
